<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-72-0512 </DOCNO><TEXT>We have measured the charge state distribution of ions generated in themetal vapor vacuum arc under a wide range of experimental conditions.The experiments were carried out using an ion source in which the metalvapor vacuum arc is used as the method of plasma production and by whicha high quality, high current beam of metal ions is produced. Charge statespectra were measured using a time-of-flight diagnostic; arc voltageswere also measured. Parameters varied include: cathode material, arccurrent, axial magnetic field strength, neutral gas pressure, and arcgeometry. 9 refs., 4 figs.</TEXT></DOC>